// Act 1: Chapel, Corridor, Deck, Mess, Passengers
const SCENES_ACT1={"chapel_waking":{"location":"The Ship's Chapel","mood":"neutral","hub":true,"text":["Ship light: yellow, overhead, not quite enough.","A small room. Iron walls painted grey over grey. A table: Bible, prayer book, and a small {ICON}. The face worn to near-nothing.","A porthole. Beyond it: the North Atlantic. Grey. Moving.","You are the ship's chaplain. You have been at sea for some time. You do not know how long."],"anamnesis":{"after":1,"text":"The {ICON} is facing the wrong direction. You are certain it was not, before.","note":"icon_wrong_direction"},"choices":[{"text":"Examine the {ICON}.","next":"chapel_icon","once":true},{"text":"Check the drawer beneath the bunk.","next":"chapel_documents","once":true},{"text":"Haircut is in the chapel. Somehow.","next":"haircut_chapel","show_if":"saw_haircut","once":true},{"text":"Haircut is in the chapel. Somehow.","next":"haircut_chapel","show_if":"saw_haircut","once":true},{"text":"Look out the porthole.","next":"chapel_porthole"},{"text":"Try to remember how long you have been aboard.","next":"chapel_memory","effect":{"doubt":1},"thought":"gnoti_seauton"},{"text":"Hold a service. The crew should have a service.","next":"vespers_approach","show_if":"merky_warned_cargo","style":"vespers"},{"text":"Go out to the corridor.","next":"corridor_first"}],"anamnesis_lines":["You have been here before. The lamp was in the same place. The {ICON} was facing a different direction.","Pavel was in the hold. You spoke to him for a long time about something you cannot quite remember."]},"chapel_icon":{"location":"The Ship's Chapel","mood":"uncanny","return_to":"chapel_waking","return_label":"Return to the chapel.","on_enter":{"note":"icon_examined","thought":"in_principio"},"text":["You lift it. Old — older than this ship by a long way. The wood warm with many hands.","The face worn to a suggestion: eyes, mouth, traces of gold. A halo that has almost entirely given itself back.","You turn it over. On the back: a script you cannot name. Not Cyrillic. Older, or different.","You know {ICON}s. You do not know this one.","You set it back down carefully."],"choices":[{"text":"Make a note of the writing.","next":"chapel_waking","effect":{"vigilance":1},"reaction":"You set it down. The script remains. You return to the room."},{"text":"Leave it. Some things you look at once.","next":"chapel_waking","reaction":"Some things you look at once. The chapel is as it was."}]},"chapel_porthole":{"location":"The Ship's Chapel","mood":"neutral","text":["You press close enough to feel the cold through the glass.","The North Atlantic does not perform. Grey and immense.","The line between water and sky is not clean. Things do not stop cleanly out here."],"choices":[{"text":"Return to the chapel.","next":"chapel_waking","style":"return"}]},"chapel_memory":{"location":"The Ship's Chapel","mood":"tense","return_to":"chapel_waking","return_label":"Stop trying.","on_enter":{"note":"crossing_noted"},"text":["You try.","A harbour — the most recent clear thing. Grey morning. Diesel and fish. Someone checking your papers without looking up.","Before that: a room. A conversation. The shape of what was said is present. The words are not.","Before that the harbour frays. You cannot locate where you were walking from.","You stop. The effort feels less like remembering and more like reaching into dark water.","A thought surfaces. Something about the structure of not-knowing."],"choices":[{"text":"Sit with that thought.","next":"chapel_waking","thought":"null_set","effect":{"doubt":1},"reaction":"You let the water recede. The chapel is still here. You are still in it."}]},"chapel_documents":{"location":"The Ship's Chapel","mood":"neutral","return_to":"chapel_waking","return_label":"Return to the chapel.","on_enter":{"flag":"found_documents"},"text":["In the small drawer beneath the bunk: a sealed envelope, already opened. Your name on it, in a handwriting you do not recognise.","Inside: one sheet of letterhead. Heritage Transfer Services, registered in Geneva. A reference number. A description of your role:","The bearer of this document is authorised to conduct liturgical authentication of Orthodox devotional objects currently in transit. Authentication requires the physical presence of an ordained minister of the relevant tradition. The bearer's signature on the attached form constitutes legal confirmation of provenance.","This is standard practice for the transit of certain categories of cultural property. The authentication is a formality.","At the bottom of the sheet, in different ink — handwritten, not printed:","Confirm only. Do not investigate further.","You read that line again.","The handwriting is not the same as the envelope. Someone added this after the document was prepared."],"choices":[{"text":"Note the discrepancy. File it.","next":"chapel_waking","effect":{"vigilance":1},"set_note":"found_documents","set_flag":"knows_authentication_role"}]},"chapel_icon_act2":{"location":"The Ship's Chapel","mood":"uncanny","return_to":"chapel_waking","return_label":"Return to the chapel.","on_enter":{"note":"mission_understood","flag":"understood_mission"},"text":["You lift it again. This time you know what you are looking at.","The script on the back — you have seen it now. In the container documentation that Sinhola translated. In the provenance records Butterantonio showed you.","It says: of the original pair. Entrusted. To be returned.","The {ICON} in your cabin was placed here as proof of ownership — and as a test. To see if the chaplain would notice. To see if the chaplain could be trusted with the transfer.","You were sent to authenticate the handoff. To ensure the object in the lower hold reaches its Western buyer.","The object belongs to people who no longer have a state. The mission is to prevent its return to them.","You sit with this for a long time."],"choices":[{"text":"You understand now. Go to the corridor.","next":"act3_approach","set_flag":"act3_unlocked"}],"text_function":true},"vespers_approach":{"location":"The Ship's Chapel","mood":"neutral","text":["You prepare the space. By evening, several people have found their way here. Merky Crabbit stands in the doorway — present, not attending. Two crew from below decks on the floor. Pavel has arrived early, in the wrong seat, warmly.","You have a reading prepared. Now you must decide what you are doing here.","Merky is watching. The crew below decks are watching. Pavel has already decided he approves."],"choices":[{"text":"Read from the Psalms of lament.","next":"vespers_traditional","effect":{"composure":1},"set_note":"vespers_traditional","set_flag":"vespers_done"},{"text":"Read from the Magnificat. The hungry filled, the rich sent away empty.","next":"vespers_liberationist","effect":{"communion":1},"set_note":"vespers_liberationist","set_flag":"vespers_done","set_flag2":"vespers_liberation"},{"text":"Read from both. Let the congregation locate themselves.","next":"vespers_ambiguous","effect":{"doubt":1},"set_note":"vespers_ambiguous","set_flag":"vespers_done"}]},"vespers_traditional":{"location":"The Ship's Chapel","mood":"neutral","return_to":"chapel_waking","return_label":"Return to the chapel.","text":["You read the psalm of lament. How long, O Lord. The voice from the pit.","Merky relaxes by a fraction. The crew listen with the patience of people who know this feeling.","Pavel is computing something.","'Good service,' Merky says, lingering. It means: you did not say anything that will cause problems.","You are not sure that is what you were ordained for."],"choices":[]},"vespers_liberationist":{"location":"The Ship's Chapel","mood":"tense","return_to":"chapel_waking","return_label":"Return to the chapel.","text":["You read the Magnificat. The proud scattered. The mighty put down. The hungry filled.","The crew below decks look up with the attention of people who did not expect to hear this here.","Merky is very still. The kind of stillness that is attention.","Pavel has tears on his face, which he does not appear to notice.","After the service, the doorway is empty. Merky did not say good evening."],"choices":[]},"vespers_ambiguous":{"location":"The Ship's Chapel","mood":"neutral","return_to":"chapel_waking","return_label":"Return to the chapel.","text":["You read both. Lament and proclamation. The ancient cry, and then the radical promise embedded in the same liturgy.","Merky nods once. The crew are quiet in a way that might be reflection or calculation.","'That was careful,' Pavel says afterward. He means: that was a decision. He noticed the decision.","You are not sure whether you withheld or offered everything and let them take what they could carry."],"choices":[]},"corridor_first":{"location":"Crew Corridor — Aft Section","mood":"neutral","hub":true,"text":["The corridor is narrow. Iron, painted many times. Overhead pipes. The engines — constant, structural.","Forward: the mess hall. Beyond the mess, further forward: the passenger section. Beyond that, the forward hold.","A ladder up leads to the main deck. A small window at the corridor's end. Through it, a slice of deck and the grey."],"choices":[{"text":"Go to the mess.","next":"mess_approach"},{"text":"Go to the passenger section.","next":"passenger_corridor"},{"text":"Go to the sick bay.","next":"sick_bay"},{"text":"Go up to the main deck.","next":"main_deck"},{"text":"Look through the corridor window.","next":"corridor_window","once":true},{"text":"One of the crew has been sitting alone. This is the work.","next":"crew_pastoral","once":true},{"text":"Merky is in the mess again. They look like they have a question.","next":"merky_cover_probe","show_if":"merky_warned_cargo","hide_if":"visited_merky_cover_probe","once":true},{"text":"Go to the chapel. The crew needs a service.","next":"vespers_approach","show_if":"merky_warned_cargo","hide_if":"vespers_done","style":"vespers"},{"text":"Return to the chapel.","next":"chapel_waking","style":"return"}]},"corridor_window":{"location":"Crew Corridor — Aft Section","mood":"uncanny","return_to":"corridor_first","return_label":"Step back.","on_enter":{"flag":"saw_window"},"text":["A black cat is sitting on the railing.","This is improbable. She is long-haired, dark as deep water, conducting an evaluation.","She holds one paw up, briefly. Then she is not on the railing. You did not see her leave."],"choices":[{"text":"Go to the main deck. Look for her.","next":"main_deck","set_note":"saw_haircut_window","effect":{"vigilance":1}},{"text":"Go to the mess.","next":"mess_approach","set_note":"saw_haircut_window"},{"text":"Go below to cargo.","next":"cargo_approach","set_note":"saw_haircut_window"}]},"main_deck":{"location":"Main Deck","mood":"neutral","hub":true,"text":["Cold. More cold than you prepared for.","Iron deck, slightly wet. A working vessel. Equipment lashed. A lifeboat station to port. The wheelhouse forward and up.","The air smells of salt, something mechanical, and — very faintly — incense."],"choices":[{"text":"Walk toward the bow.","next":"deck_bow"},{"text":"Look along the port railing.","next":"deck_haircut","once":true,"hide_if":"saw_haircut"},{"text":"Approach the wheelhouse.","next":"wheelhouse_exterior"},{"text":"The railing is empty.","next":"main_deck","show_if":"saw_haircut","style":"return"},{"text":"Go back inside.","next":"corridor_first"},{"text":"Bless the ship. This is part of the work.","next":"ship_blessing","once":true},{"text":"Speak to the crew member at the railing.","next":"deck_night_crew","show_if":"vespers_done","once":true},{"text":"Haircut is on the railing. Just watching. Being. You do not approach.","next":"haircut_observation","show_if":"saw_haircut","hide_if":"visited_haircut_observation","once":true}]},"deck_bow":{"location":"Main Deck — Bow","mood":"neutral","return_to":"main_deck","return_label":"Return to the main deck.","text":["The bow cuts the water. Grey to the horizon.","The wind asks nothing of you.","Peripherally: a cat on the port railing. Long-haired, black, balanced there with the equanimity of something that does not understand why this weather would present a problem."],"choices":[{"text":"Go to the cat.","next":"deck_haircut","hide_if":"saw_haircut"},{"text":"Watch her from here.","next":"deck_haircut_watch","hide_if":"saw_haircut","effect":{"vigilance":1}},{"text":"Go inside.","next":"corridor_first"}]},"deck_haircut":{"location":"Main Deck — Port Railing","mood":"uncanny","art":"haircut","on_enter":{"note":"saw_haircut","flag":"saw_haircut"},"text":["You approach. She is large, long-haired, black the way deep water is black.","Her purr begins: a low rasp that sounds like it has been through a great deal.","She lifts one paw. Holds it. The gesture slightly beside itself.","Her eyes: recognition older than this crossing. She has assessed you.","Then she is not on the railing. The answer, you will learn, was yes."],"choices":[{"text":"Go below.","next":"cargo_approach"},{"text":"Go to the mess.","next":"mess_approach"},{"text":"Approach the wheelhouse.","next":"wheelhouse_exterior"},{"text":"Return to the deck.","next":"main_deck","style":"return"}]},"deck_haircut_watch":{"location":"Main Deck — Bow","mood":"uncanny","art":"haircut","on_enter":{"note":"saw_haircut","flag":"saw_haircut"},"text":["She is large. Long-haired, black the way the space between things is black.","Her purr reaches you. A low rasp that sounds like it has been through a great deal.","She lifts one paw. Holds it — the gesture slightly beside itself. Sets it down.","She looks at you. Recognition older than this crossing. Patient. Complete.","Then she is not on the railing. You did not see her leave."],"choices":[{"text":"Go below. To cargo.","next":"cargo_approach"},{"text":"Go to the mess.","next":"mess_approach"},{"text":"Approach the wheelhouse.","next":"wheelhouse_exterior"},{"text":"Return to the deck.","next":"main_deck","style":"return"}]},"deck_night_crew":{"location":"Main Deck","mood":"neutral","return_to":"main_deck","return_label":"Return to the deck.","on_enter":{"flag":"deck_night_done"},"text":["A crew member is doing something technical at the far railing — maintenance, or inspection, or the particular occupation of someone who needed to be outside.","They see you approach and do not stop what they are doing.","'Chaplain,' they say. Not a greeting. A naming.","You stand near them for a moment. The sea is doing what it does.","'Did it help?' they ask, eventually. 'The service.' They do not look up.","You tell them the truth — whatever that is for you, about that service.","'Good,' they say. And then they say nothing else. But something in their posture has shifted very slightly. The kind of shift that is also a form of gratitude."],"choices":[{"text":"Leave them to the maintenance.","next":"main_deck","effect":{"communion":1},"reaction":"The sea continues. The ship continues.","show_if":"vespers_done"}]},"wheelhouse_exterior":{"location":"Main Deck — Wheelhouse Approach","mood":"neutral","return_to":"main_deck","return_label":"Return to the main deck.","text":["The wheelhouse is glassed in, elevated. Through the salt-hazed windows: the helm, the instruments.","A man leans against the exterior rail, looking at the water. He has the quality of someone who is very good at not doing anything — as if the not-doing is itself a practice.","He has not looked at you. You have the impression he registered your arrival some time ago."],"choices":[{"text":"Approach him.","next":"vance_meet","requires_stat":["composure",2]},{"text":"Stay back. Watch first.","next":"vance_watch","effect":{"vigilance":1}}]},"vance_watch":{"location":"Main Deck — Wheelhouse Approach","mood":"neutral","on_enter":{"flag":"saw_vance"},"return_to":"main_deck","return_label":"Return to the main deck.","text":["He is tall. Work-worn in a way that is different from the other crew.","A black cat — Haircut — appears and sits near his feet. He does not look down at her. She does not look up at him. They occupy the space with the ease of long practice.","He knows the cat's name. The cat knows his. You have not heard anyone tell either of them."],"choices":[{"text":"Approach him now.","next":"vance_meet","requires_stat":["composure",2]},{"text":"Leave them to it. Go inside.","next":"corridor_first"}]},"vance_meet":{"location":"Main Deck — Wheelhouse Approach","mood":"neutral","on_enter":{"note":"met_vance","flag":"met_vance"},"text":["He turns to look at you before you reach him. Not startled — simply done waiting.","'Chaplain,' he says. Not a greeting and not a question.","'Vance Landstorm,' he says after a pause. 'I have been on this vessel since before you were ordained.'","Haircut sits at his feet, conducting her own assessment of the horizon.","'She has been asking about you,' he says. He does not specify who he means."],"choices":[{"text":"'She? Who do you mean?'","next":"vance_she","effect":{"vigilance":1}},{"text":"'How long have you been on this route?'","next":"vance_route","effect":{"communion":1}},{"text":"Say nothing. Let him continue.","next":"vance_silence","effect":{"composure":1}}]},"vance_she":{"location":"Main Deck — Wheelhouse Approach","mood":"neutral","return_to":"main_deck","return_label":"Return.","text":["'The cat,' he says.","He does not look at her when he says it, which makes it clearer that he means more than the cat.","'She assesses everyone who boards. She has been watching you since before you noticed her.' A pause. 'The previous chaplain did not notice her.'","He stops talking. He is done elaborating on this. You may push or leave it."],"choices":[{"text":"'What happened to the previous chaplain?'","next":"vance_previous","effect":{"vigilance":1}},{"text":"Leave him to the water.","next":"corridor_first","reaction":"You leave him at the railing. Haircut does not move when you pass."}]},"vance_route":{"location":"Main Deck — Wheelhouse Approach","mood":"neutral","return_to":"main_deck","return_label":"Return.","text":["'Long enough that I have stopped counting,' he says.","'The ship changes on every crossing. Not the hull. The ship.'","'This crossing is different,' he says. Not as observation. As information."],"choices":[{"text":"'Different how?'","next":"vance_different","effect":{"doubt":1}},{"text":"Leave him to the water.","next":"corridor_first","reaction":"He turns back to the water. You have your information."}]},"vance_silence":{"location":"Main Deck — Wheelhouse Approach","mood":"neutral","return_to":"main_deck","return_label":"Return.","text":["He waits. Then he continues.","'There is a passenger in the forward section who has been trying to access the wheelhouse. Says he is a lawyer.'","'The cargo manifest has an entry that should not be there. I have seen it before.' He stops.","'Before what?' you ask.","He does not answer. He turns back to the water."],"choices":[{"text":"Go find the passenger.","next":"passenger_corridor","effect":{"vigilance":1},"reaction":"Vance does not watch you go. He is already looking at the water again."},{"text":"Go find the manifest. Cargo.","next":"cargo_approach","effect":{"vigilance":1},"reaction":"The container is in the lower forward hold. You know the manifest number from the briefing."},{"text":"Leave him to it.","next":"corridor_first"},{"text":"[Suspicion] 'Before what?' you say again. More carefully this time.","next":"vance_before_what","requires_charism":"suspicion","effect":{"vigilance":2}}]},"vance_previous":{"location":"Main Deck — Wheelhouse Approach","mood":"tense","return_to":"main_deck","return_label":"Return.","text":["He is quiet for long enough that you wonder if he heard you.","'Left the ship,' he says finally. 'Partway through a crossing.'","'This was some time ago. A different kind of crossing than this one. Though I was not sure I understood that at the time.'","Haircut presses her side against his leg briefly. He does not look down."],"choices":[{"text":"Leave him to the water.","next":"corridor_first"}]},"vance_different":{"location":"Main Deck — Wheelhouse Approach","mood":"uncanny","return_to":"main_deck","return_label":"Return.","text":["'The cargo,' he says. 'Usually I know what we are carrying by weight and feel. This crossing I do not. Something in the lower hold accounts for itself differently.'","'And the passenger in the forward section. He has been on this ship before. I know his hands. He does not know I know.'","He turns and looks at you directly for the first time.","'And you,' he says. 'You are not what the last chaplain was.' He holds your gaze. Then he is done. Back to the water."],"choices":[{"text":"Go to the passenger section.","next":"passenger_corridor","effect":{"vigilance":1}},{"text":"Go to cargo.","next":"cargo_approach","effect":{"vigilance":1}}]},"vance_before_what":{"location":"Main Deck — Wheelhouse Approach","mood":"tense","return_to":"main_deck","return_label":"Return to the main deck.","text":["He turns to look at you.","You have been paying attention to him. He notices that you have been paying attention to him. Something shifts.","'Before a previous chaplain left partway through a crossing,' he says. 'Before the manifest had an entry I could not account for. Before I understood that some crossings are decided before they begin.'","A very long pause.","'The container in the lower hold,' he says. 'It has been on this ship before. Under a different manifest number. I recognised it by the lock housing — it was modified after manufacture. I know the modification because I watched someone make it.'","He turns back to the water.","'I did not ask questions then,' he says. 'I am not asking them now. But I am telling you.'","He is done."],"choices":[{"text":"Go to cargo. Now.","next":"cargo_approach","effect":{"vigilance":2},"set_flag":"vance_told_you","set_note":"vance_told_you"},{"text":"Go to the passenger section first.","next":"passenger_corridor","set_flag":"vance_told_you"}]},"mess_approach":{"location":"Crew Mess","mood":"neutral","text":["Warmth, and the smell of something cooked many times in the same pot.","A crew member — fifties, weathered — sits with a mug. Two others at the far end whose conversation stops when you appear.","The crew knows what a ship's chaplain is for. They are uncertain whether they want it."],"choices":[{"text":"Haircut is in the mess. Somehow.","next":"haircut_mess","show_if":"saw_haircut","once":true},{"text":"Haircut is in the mess. Somehow.","next":"haircut_mess","show_if":"saw_haircut","once":true},{"text":"Pour yourself something and sit near the first mate.","next":"merky_meet","effect":{"communion":1}},{"text":"Introduce yourself to the table.","next":"merky_meet"},{"text":"Find a corner. Wait for them to come to you.","next":"merky_observe","effect":{"vigilance":1}},{"text":"This can wait. Go below.","next":"cargo_approach"},{"text":"Sit nearby. Watch the crew.","next":"mess_crew_atmosphere","once":true},{"text":"Merky has a request — the crew needs something.","next":"merky_denomination_test","show_if":"act2_unlocked","hide_if":"visited_merky_denomination_test","once":true},{"text":"Continue to the passenger section.","next":"passenger_corridor"},{"text":"Go back to the corridor.","next":"corridor_first","style":"return"}],"anamnesis_lines":["Merky Crabbit. First mate. You know that name. You knew it before they said it."]},"mess_crew_atmosphere":{"location":"Crew Mess","mood":"neutral","return_to":"mess_approach","return_label":"Return to the mess.","text":["Two crew members you have not spoken to are playing cards at the far end of the table. They do not acknowledge you, which is its own kind of acknowledgement.","One of them — older, with the particular stillness of someone who has crossed this route many times — glances at you briefly. Then back to the cards.","The ship sounds different in the mess than anywhere else. The engines are louder. The smell of the last meal is still present. There is a quality of people occupying a space that is also a machine.","You understand, sitting here, that the ship does not care about the container. The ship cares about the crossing. These are the same thing but they are not."],"choices":[{"text":"Leave them to their cards.","next":"mess_approach","style":"return","reaction":"They do not watch you go."}]},"merky_meet":{"location":"Crew Mess","mood":"neutral","on_enter":{"note":"merky_introduced"},"text":["'Merky Crabbit,' they say, without looking up from the mug. 'First mate.'","A pause. They let the title settle. Then they look at you.","'Chaplain. Right. What do you need?'"],"choices":[{"text":"'How long have you been on this route?'","next":"merky_route","effect":{"communion":1}},{"text":"'What should I know about this ship?'","next":"merky_beat_ship","effect":{"vigilance":1}},{"text":"Say nothing. Let them decide what comes next.","next":"merky_silence","reaction":"You sit with your coffee. The silence is not uncomfortable. It is a statement."},{"text":"[Withholding] Give them nothing. Let the silence speak.","next":"merky_withholding","requires_charism":"withholding","effect":{"composure":2}}]},"merky_observe":{"location":"Crew Mess","mood":"neutral","on_enter":{"note":"merky_introduced"},"text":["You find a corner. The two at the far end resume — something about the cargo manifest, a discrepancy in the count.","Eventually the one with the mug comes over.","'Merky Crabbit. First mate. You have been sitting there like you are waiting for something.'"],"choices":[{"text":"'I was. Now I am here.'","next":"merky_meet_cont","effect":{"composure":1}},{"text":"'I heard something about a discrepancy.'","next":"merky_discrepancy_open","effect":{"vigilance":1}}]},"merky_meet_cont":{"location":"Crew Mess","mood":"neutral","text":["'Huh,' Merky says. This appears to conclude something.","'Merky Crabbit. First mate. What do you need, Chaplain?'"],"choices":[{"text":"'How long have you been on this route?'","next":"merky_route","effect":{"communion":1}},{"text":"'What should I know about this ship?'","next":"merky_ship","effect":{"vigilance":1}},{"text":"Nothing for now. Go.","next":"corridor_first"}]},"merky_beat_ship":{"location":"Crew Mess","mood":"neutral","text":["Merky is quiet for a moment. The kind of quiet that means they are deciding how much to say.","They refill their mug. Do not offer you any.","'She's older than she looks. Or looks older than she is. I've never settled which.'"],"choices":[{"text":"Wait. Let them continue.","next":"merky_ship","effect":{"composure":1},"reaction":"Merky decides to continue. You gave them the space for it."},{"text":"'The crew?'","next":"merky_ship","effect":{"communion":1},"reaction":"Merky nods. A practical question. They can work with practical."},{"text":"'And the cargo?'","next":"merky_ship","effect":{"vigilance":1},"reaction":"A small pause. Then: 'Cargo is none of your business.' But they keep talking."}]},"merky_route":{"location":"Crew Mess","mood":"neutral","text":["'Long enough,' Merky says. 'Long enough that I have stopped counting crossings and started counting something else. Have not found the right unit yet.'","A pause. They set down the mug.","'And you? First time on a working vessel? You do not look like cargo.'"],"choices":[{"text":"'I requested this posting. I had my reasons.'","next":"merky_route_b","effect":{"vigilance":1},"reaction":"Merky looks at you with the careful attention of someone recalibrating an initial read.","cover_set":{"key":"posting","value":"posting_requested"},"set_note":"cover_posting_requested","hide_if":"cover_posting_set"},{"text":"'I was assigned. No one asked me.'","next":"merky_route_b","effect":{"composure":1},"reaction":"Something in Merky's posture settles — the particular ease of someone whose assumption has been confirmed.","cover_set":{"key":"posting","value":"posting_assigned"},"set_note":"cover_posting_assigned","hide_if":"cover_posting_set"},{"text":"'I needed to be somewhere else.'","next":"merky_route_b","effect":{"doubt":1},"reaction":"Merky considers this for a moment with the patience of someone who has seen many versions of that sentence.","cover_set":{"key":"posting","value":"posting_escape"},"set_note":"cover_posting_escape","hide_if":"cover_posting_set"},{"text":"'Someone asked for me specifically. I still do not know who.'","next":"merky_route_b","effect":{"communion":1},"reaction":"Merky looks at you with something that is not quite surprise. 'That is unusual,' they say, not entirely to you.","cover_set":{"key":"posting","value":"posting_summoned"},"set_note":"cover_posting_summoned","hide_if":"cover_posting_set"},{"text":"[Same answer as before.]","next":"merky_route_b","effect":{"composure":1},"reaction":"Merky accepts the repetition. Nothing in their face suggests they do or do not believe you.","show_if":"cover_posting_set"}]},"merky_route_b":{"location":"Crew Mess","mood":"neutral","text":["'Before the collar,' they say. 'What were you?'"],"choices":[{"text":"'A teacher.'","next":"merky_cargo_warning","effect":{"communion":1},"reaction":"'Teachers end up in strange places,' Merky says. Not unkindly.","cover_set":{"key":"background","value":"bg_teacher"},"set_note":"cover_bg_teacher","hide_if":"cover_background_set"},{"text":"'Medical work.'","next":"merky_cargo_warning","effect":{"vigilance":1},"reaction":"Merky glances at your hands. Then back at your face. Some kind of assessment completed.","cover_set":{"key":"background","value":"bg_medical"},"set_note":"cover_bg_medical","hide_if":"cover_background_set"},{"text":"'Civil service. Minor.'","next":"merky_cargo_warning","effect":{"composure":1},"reaction":"Merky nods. The kind of nod that means: that explains some things and raises others.","cover_set":{"key":"background","value":"bg_functionary"},"set_note":"cover_bg_functionary","hide_if":"cover_background_set"},{"text":"'A student. For a very long time.'","next":"merky_cargo_warning","effect":{"doubt":1},"reaction":"Merky is quiet for a moment. 'And then,' they say, as if completing a sentence you had not finished.","cover_set":{"key":"background","value":"bg_scholar"},"set_note":"cover_bg_scholar","hide_if":"cover_background_set"},{"text":"[Same answer as before.]","next":"merky_cargo_warning","effect":{"composure":1},"reaction":"Merky nods. You have said it twice now. It is beginning to sound true, which is the point.","show_if":"cover_background_set"}]},"merky_cargo_warning":{"location":"Crew Mess","mood":"tense","on_enter":{"note":"merky_warned_cargo","flag":"merky_warned_cargo"},"text":["Merky nods. Stands.","'Stay out of cargo,' they say. Not quite a warning. 'There is a passenger down there who should not be. Keeps saying he is lost. He talks about God. Thought that might be your department.'","'Also: the forward section has someone who keeps trying to reach the wheelhouse. Maritime lawyer, he says.' A pause. 'He is not.'"],"choices":[{"text":"Go to cargo now.","next":"cargo_approach","effect":{"vigilance":1},"reaction":"You leave Merky to the counter. The ladder down to cargo is at the end of the aft corridor."},{"text":"Go to the passenger section first.","next":"passenger_corridor","effect":{"vigilance":1},"reaction":"You head forward. If there is a lawyer with a briefcase asking about the manifest, that is a conversation worth having before cargo."},{"text":"'What tradition did you declare the ship maintains?'","next":"merky_tradition"},{"text":"'Thank you.' Go to the deck.","next":"main_deck","reaction":"Merky turns back to the counter. You have your bearings now."}]},"merky_ship":{"location":"Crew Mess","mood":"neutral","text":["'She is older than she looks. Or looks older than she is.' A drink. 'Crew is solid. Cargo is none of your business. Crossing takes as long as it takes.'","A pause. 'There is a passenger in the forward section who has been asking questions he does not have the background for. About the manifest. About the route.'"],"choices":[{"text":"'What kind of questions, specifically?'","next":"merky_butterantonio_detail","effect":{"vigilance":1},"reaction":"Merky sits back down. If you want to know the specifics, they will tell you the specifics."},{"text":"'Sounds like chaplain work.'","next":"merky_route","effect":{"communion":1},"reaction":"Something in Merky's posture shifts — a slight opening. They had expected deflection."}]},"merky_tradition":{"location":"Crew Mess","mood":"neutral","text":["'We maintain whatever the company told us to. Which is none.' A pause. 'What tradition are you?'"],"choices":[{"text":"'Orthodox.'","next":"merky_tradition_exit","reaction":"Merky looks at you for a moment. 'That explains some things about the assignment,' they say. Then they stop, as if that was more than they meant to share.","cover_set":{"key":"denomination","value":"denom_orthodox"},"set_note":"cover_denom_orthodox","hide_if":"cover_denomination_set","set_flag":"merky_noted_orthodox"},{"text":"'Protestant.'","next":"merky_tradition_exit","reaction":"'Protestant.' Merky nods. An ecumenical answer. Not specific enough to mean anything, which may be the point.","effect":{"composure":1},"cover_set":{"key":"denomination","value":"denom_protestant"},"set_note":"cover_denom_protestant","hide_if":"cover_denomination_set"},{"text":"'Ecumenical.'","next":"merky_tradition_exit","reaction":"'Ecumenical,' Merky repeats. The word lands with the sound of a door closing carefully.","effect":{"doubt":1},"cover_set":{"key":"denomination","value":"denom_ecumenical"},"set_note":"cover_denom_ecumenical","hide_if":"cover_denomination_set"},{"text":"'Catholic.'","next":"merky_tradition_exit","reaction":"Merky nods. 'The company usually sends Protestant.' A pause. 'Not a complaint.'","cover_set":{"key":"denomination","value":"denom_catholic"},"set_note":"cover_denom_catholic","hide_if":"cover_denomination_set"},{"text":"[Same answer as before.]","next":"merky_tradition_exit","reaction":"Merky nods. You have said it twice. That is how covers are maintained.","effect":{"composure":1},"show_if":"cover_denomination_set"}]},"merky_tradition_exit":{"location":"Crew Mess","mood":"neutral","text":["Merky stands. The conversation has been concluded — on their end, at least.","'Stay out of cargo,' they say again, on the way out. 'Not a prohibition. Just a word.'","You are alone with the coffee. The mess smells of a meal made some time ago."],"choices":[{"text":"Go to cargo.","next":"cargo_approach","effect":{"vigilance":1}},{"text":"Go to the passenger section.","next":"passenger_corridor"},{"text":"Go to the deck.","next":"main_deck"},{"text":"Return to the corridor.","next":"corridor_first","style":"return"}]},"merky_butterantonio_detail":{"location":"Crew Mess","mood":"neutral","return_to":"mess_approach","return_label":"Return to the mess.","text":["'Questions about the cargo manifest,' Merky says. 'Specific questions. He wanted to know the declared value on a particular container in the lower forward hold. He knew the manifest number. He knew the origin code.' A pause. 'He did not explain how he knew these things.'","'He is in the forward passenger section. Briefcase. Two pairs of glasses. He introduced himself as a maritime lawyer.' Merky's tone suggests this explanation does not explain very much.","'He is not violent. He is not obviously dangerous. He is just — present, in the way of someone who has a specific purpose and is waiting for the right moment to pursue it.'","A pause.","'And there is the other one. In cargo. Talks about God. That one might actually be your department.'"],"choices":[{"text":"Go to the forward passenger section.","next":"passenger_corridor","effect":{"vigilance":1}},{"text":"Go to cargo instead.","next":"cargo_approach","effect":{"vigilance":1}},{"text":"Thank Merky. Go to the deck.","next":"main_deck"}]},"merky_silence":{"location":"Crew Mess","mood":"neutral","text":["Merky looks at you for a long moment. You look back.","'Huh,' they say eventually.","'Do not go below without a reason you would say out loud,' they say, walking away.","You are alone with old coffee and the sense of having passed a test."],"choices":[{"text":"Go below to cargo.","next":"cargo_approach","effect":{"composure":1},"reaction":"You go below. You have a reason. You would say it out loud if asked."},{"text":"Go to the main deck.","next":"main_deck","reaction":"The air on deck will be cold. That seems appropriate."},{"text":"Go to the passenger section.","next":"passenger_corridor","reaction":"Forward, then. The passenger section. Someone there with a briefcase and questions."}]},"merky_withholding":{"location":"Crew Mess","mood":"neutral","return_to":"mess_approach","return_label":"Return to the mess.","text":["You give Merky nothing.","Not hostility. Not warmth. The particular quality of a space that has been emptied of intention. You sit with your coffee and you are simply there, present without pressing.","Merky watches you for a long time. Then they stop watching and start thinking. You can see it happen.","'There is a passenger in cargo who should not be there,' they say finally, as if you had asked. 'Talks about God. Thought that might be your department.'","They stand. 'I did not ask your background,' they say. 'I will not.' A pause. 'That is either professional courtesy or something else. I have not decided which.'","They leave. You have their respect, or something that functions like it."],"on_enter":{"note":"merky_warned_cargo","flag":"cover_posting_set"},"choices":[{"text":"Go to cargo now.","next":"cargo_approach","effect":{"composure":1}},{"text":"Go to the deck first.","next":"main_deck"}]},"passenger_corridor":{"location":"Passenger Corridor — Forward Section","mood":"neutral","hub":true,"text":["A narrower corridor. Wood panelling over iron. A strip of carpet that has absorbed decades of salt water.","Three cabin doors. A common area at the end — a table, two chairs, a lamp built for a different ship.","From the common area: the sound of papers being moved.","The forward hold is past this section. You can feel the ship's bow in the sound of the water through the hull."],"choices":[{"text":"Go to the common area.","next":"passenger_common"},{"text":"Listen at the cabin doors.","next":"passenger_cabins","effect":{"vigilance":1}},{"text":"Try Cabin 2.","next":"cabin_2_approach","show_if":"act2_unlocked","requires_stat":["vigilance",2]},{"text":"Go back to the crew section.","next":"corridor_first","style":"return"},{"text":"Go further forward. The hold is past the passenger section.","next":"cargo_approach","show_if":"merky_warned_cargo"},{"text":"The forward hold is past here. You are not ready yet.","next":"cargo_not_ready","hide_if":"merky_warned_cargo"}]},"passenger_cabins":{"location":"Passenger Corridor — Forward Section","mood":"neutral","return_to":"passenger_corridor","return_label":"Return to the corridor.","text":["Cabin 1: nothing. Or the controlled silence of someone who knows they might be listened to.","Cabin 2: movement. Something being shifted. A muttering — not distressed. Computational.","Cabin 3: nothing at all. A quality of nothing-at-all that is different from emptiness.","You note all three."],"choices":[{"text":"Go to the common area.","next":"passenger_common","effect":{"vigilance":1}}]},"passenger_common":{"location":"Passenger Common Area","mood":"neutral","hub":true,"text":["At the table: a man in his fifties with a briefcase open in front of him. Papers arranged in a pattern that is either methodical or chaotic. He has two pairs of glasses and is wearing one of each type simultaneously.","He looks up. He has the face of someone who has been waiting to be interrupted by exactly you."],"choices":[{"text":"Introduce yourself.","next":"butterantonio_meet"},{"text":"Ask what he is working on.","next":"butterantonio_papers","effect":{"vigilance":1}},{"text":"Look at the notice board on the wall.","next":"passenger_notice","once":true}]},"passenger_notice":{"location":"Passenger Common Area","mood":"neutral","return_to":"passenger_common","return_label":"Return to the common area.","text":["A notice board. Ship regulations, an outdated schedule, a hand-drawn map.","Someone has added annotations in pencil — small, careful. Not in English. Not in any language you can immediately place.","Some annotations mark rooms that do not appear on the printed layout."],"choices":[{"text":"Make a mental note.","next":"passenger_common","effect":{"vigilance":1},"set_flag":"saw_notice_map"}]},"butterantonio_meet":{"location":"Passenger Common Area","mood":"neutral","on_enter":{"note":"met_butterantonio","flag":"met_butterantonio"},"text":["'Chaplain!' he says, with the relief of someone who has been waiting for the right professional. 'Excellent. I am Craigslist Butterantonio, maritime law, semi-retired but not in any way that affects my standing.'","He gestures at the other chair. You sit.","'I have been attempting to access the ship's official documentation for three days,' he says, 'and I want to be honest about that, because I think honesty is going to be important in whatever this is.'","His two pairs of glasses catch the lamplight."],"choices":[{"text":"'What documentation?'","next":"butterantonio_docs","effect":{"vigilance":1}},{"text":"'Whatever what is?'","next":"butterantonio_whatever","effect":{"doubt":1}},{"text":"'Are you all right? You seem agitated.'","next":"butterantonio_state","effect":{"communion":1}}]},"butterantonio_papers":{"location":"Passenger Common Area","mood":"neutral","on_enter":{"note":"met_butterantonio","flag":"met_butterantonio"},"text":["He looks up before you have spoken. The cargo manifest, he says. An anomaly. He has been cross-referencing it with the ship's registry and what he believes to be a secondary manifest that someone went to some trouble to obscure.","'I am Craigslist Butterantonio. Maritime law. Two pairs of glasses. You are the chaplain. Good. I was hoping there would be a chaplain.'"],"choices":[{"text":"'What anomaly?'","next":"butterantonio_docs","effect":{"vigilance":1}},{"text":"'Why were you hoping for a chaplain?'","next":"butterantonio_whatever","effect":{"doubt":1}},{"text":"'What secondary manifest?'","next":"butterantonio_docs","effect":{"vigilance":2}}]},"butterantonio_docs":{"location":"Passenger Common Area","mood":"tense","return_to":"passenger_common","return_label":"Return to the common area.","text":["'The manifest lists a sealed container as: archival material, academic, declared value nominal. That phrase — declared value nominal — is a legal flag.' He adjusts his reading glasses. 'It means the shipper has declared the value low. But the insurance documentation lists a much higher figure. Under a category I have only seen used twice in forty years.'","'What category?' you ask.","'Culturally significant material, provenance disputed.' He lets that settle. 'Someone is moving something that belongs, arguably, to someone else. Possibly a nation-state.'","'I am not here to stop it,' he says carefully. 'I am here to understand it. The law has nuances.'"],"choices":[{"text":"'Who hired you?'","next":"butterantonio_client","effect":{"vigilance":1}},{"text":"'What do you think it is?'","next":"butterantonio_guess","effect":{"doubt":1}},{"text":"Leave him to it. Go to cargo.","next":"cargo_approach","effect":{"vigilance":1},"set_flag":"butterantonio_knows","reaction":"You leave him with his papers. The ladder to cargo is aft. You know the manifest number now."}]},"butterantonio_whatever":{"location":"Passenger Common Area","mood":"neutral","return_to":"passenger_common","return_label":"Return.","text":["'I have been on a number of ships and I have never been on one that felt like this one. The same answer keeps arriving: this ship is paying attention.'","'Ships do not pay attention,' you say.","'No,' he agrees. 'They do not. And yet.' He polishes a lens. 'And then there is the manifest question. And the fact that someone was in my cabin last night. Nothing taken. Nothing moved. But someone was there.'"],"choices":[{"text":"'What is in the manifest?'","next":"butterantonio_docs","effect":{"vigilance":1}},{"text":"'Did you see who it was?'","next":"butterantonio_visitor","effect":{"vigilance":1}}]},"butterantonio_state":{"location":"Passenger Common Area","mood":"neutral","return_to":"passenger_common","return_label":"Return.","text":["'Yes,' he says. 'Somewhat.' He takes both pairs of glasses off. Without them he looks older and more certain of something.","'I have seen things moved across water that should not have been moved. This crossing feels like one of those. I would like to be wrong.'","He picks up a paper and puts it down again.","'I would like to be wrong,' he repeats, 'but I am not often wrong.'"],"choices":[{"text":"'Tell me about the manifest.'","next":"butterantonio_docs","effect":{"vigilance":1}},{"text":"'You will not be alone in whatever this is.'","next":"butterantonio_reassure","effect":{"communion":1}}]},"butterantonio_client":{"location":"Passenger Common Area","mood":"tense","return_to":"passenger_common","return_label":"Return.","text":["'I cannot tell you that. Privilege.' A pause. 'My client is not on this ship. My client's interests and this ship's current manifest are in direct opposition.'","'Why does the chaplain change things?' you ask.","'Because the chaplain is the only person on this vessel who might understand what is actually at stake. Not legally. Theologically.'"],"choices":[{"text":"'What is at stake, theologically?'","next":"butterantonio_stakes","effect":{"doubt":1}},{"text":"Go to cargo. Find out yourself.","next":"cargo_approach","effect":{"vigilance":1},"set_flag":"butterantonio_knows","reaction":"You stand. He watches you go without comment. He knows where you are heading."}]},"butterantonio_guess":{"location":"Passenger Common Area","mood":"uncanny","return_to":"passenger_common","return_label":"Return.","text":["'Something that was taken during a period when taking was easy. An object of resonance — not monetary. The other kind.'","'An object that means something to a great many people who are not currently in a position to say so. History is unstable. What was taken may become returnable.'","'There is a thought I have been sitting with for three days. About what things are worth and who gets to decide.'"],"choices":[{"text":"'Let me hear it.'","next":"butterantonio_thought","effect":{"doubt":1},"thought":"sobornost"},{"text":"Go to cargo.","next":"cargo_approach","effect":{"vigilance":1},"set_flag":"butterantonio_knows"}]},"butterantonio_thought":{"location":"Passenger Common Area","mood":"neutral","return_to":"passenger_common","return_label":"Return.","text":["'There are objects that accumulate the belief of generations. Not necessarily relics in the religious sense — though sometimes. Objects around which a collective understanding has crystallised. They hold what the group knows about itself.'","'When those objects are removed, the group loses not just the thing. Something in the structure of collective knowing. And when they are returned —' He stops. 'That is what I do not know.'","'I suspect you might know. Or be on the way to knowing.'"],"choices":[{"text":"Go to cargo.","next":"cargo_approach","effect":{"vigilance":1},"set_flag":"butterantonio_knows"}]},"butterantonio_visitor":{"location":"Passenger Common Area","mood":"uncanny","return_to":"passenger_common","return_label":"Return.","text":["'I did not see anyone,' he says. 'I heard the door. The quality of the air change. I got up. No one there.'","'But there was a cat sitting in the middle of the floor. A large black cat with long hair. She looked at me for thirty seconds and then left through a door that was not open.'","'She was assessing something,' he says. 'I have been trying to decide what to do with that information.'"],"choices":[{"text":"'That is Haircut,' you say. 'She does that.'","next":"butterantonio_haircut","requires_flag":"saw_haircut","effect":{"communion":1}}]},"butterantonio_haircut":{"location":"Passenger Common Area","mood":"neutral","return_to":"passenger_common","return_label":"Return.","text":["He stares at you. 'You know the cat,' he says.","'She was assessing you,' you say. 'She does that with everyone.'","'And?' he says. 'What is the verdict?'","'She has never been wrong,' you say. You are not certain how you know this. But you know it.","He considers this for a long time. Then he opens his briefcase.","'All right,' he says. 'Sit down. Let me tell you everything.'"],"choices":[{"text":"Sit down. Let him tell you everything.","next":"butterantonio_docs","effect":{"vigilance":1,"communion":1}}]},"butterantonio_reassure":{"location":"Passenger Common Area","mood":"neutral","return_to":"passenger_common","return_label":"Return.","text":["'That is a very chaplain thing to say,' he says. 'I mean that as a compliment.'","'I do not need reassurance. I need someone to know what I know. In case something happens to the knowing.'","He spreads his papers on the table. Let me show you the manifest, he says."],"choices":[{"text":"Let him show you.","next":"butterantonio_docs","effect":{"vigilance":1}}]},"butterantonio_stakes":{"location":"Passenger Common Area","mood":"tense","return_to":"passenger_common","return_label":"Return.","text":["'The question of what things belong to. Theologically: the question of what can be owned. Whether things that carry the weight of a people's self-understanding can be transferred. Whether that transfer is valid in a sense that is not legal.'","'There is an object in the lower hold that belongs — in some sense prior to law — to a great many people who no longer have a state. Or had one, briefly, and then lost it. And who have been — I think the word is waiting.'","'You are the chaplain,' he says. 'You understand waiting.'"],"choices":[{"text":"'Tell me everything you know.'","next":"butterantonio_docs","effect":{"doubt":1,"vigilance":1}},{"text":"Go to cargo.","next":"cargo_approach","effect":{"vigilance":1},"set_flag":"butterantonio_knows","reaction":"You leave the common area. He is still writing when you go."}]},"ship_blessing":{"location":"Main Deck","mood":"neutral","return_to":"main_deck","return_label":"Return to the deck without ceremony.","on_enter":{"flag":"performed_blessing"},"text":["Ships have been blessed since before any tradition that currently blesses them.","You stand at the bow. The wind is considerable. You speak the words — whichever words feel true, from whichever tradition you have declared.","Two crew members, passing with equipment, slow down. Then stop. One of them removes their hat.","The ship continues to move through the water, which it would have done regardless. But the crew member who removed their hat puts it back on with a slightly different expression. Something has been acknowledged.","This is most of what a blessing is."],"choices":[{"text":"Return to the deck.","next":"main_deck","effect":{"communion":1}}]},"crew_pastoral":{"location":"Crew Quarters","mood":"neutral","return_to":"corridor_first","return_label":"Return to the corridor.","text":["One of the crew from the far end of the mess table. You have seen them twice now sitting alone with a mug that has gone cold.","You knock on the open door of their bunk. They look up.","'I don't need a priest,' they say. Then, after a moment: 'Is it obvious?'","'Something is carrying you,' you say.","They are quiet for a long time.","'My mother is ill,' they say finally. 'On shore. I took this crossing because we needed the money. I will not be back before —' They stop.","You sit with them for a while. You do not say that it will be all right. You do not know if it will be all right. You say that she knows they are thinking of her. You say that love crosses water."],"choices":[{"text":"Stay a little longer.","next":"crew_pastoral_stay","effect":{"communion":1}}]},"crew_pastoral_stay":{"location":"Crew Quarters","mood":"neutral","return_to":"corridor_first","return_label":"Return to the corridor.","text":["You stay.","They do not talk much more. But having someone present for the not-talking seems to be the thing that was needed.","When you get up to leave, they say: 'The passenger in cargo. The one who talks about God. I saw him this morning. He looked — purposeful. Like someone who knows where they are going even when they don't know where they are.'","A pause.","'I thought you should know. He's been asking about the container with the academic materials. Not to anyone official. Just — asking.'"],"choices":[{"text":"[Cover: a moment of sincerity. Tell them something true about yourself.]","next":"crew_pastoral_sincere","requires_charism":"cover","effect":{"communion":1}}]},"crew_pastoral_sincere":{"location":"Crew Quarters","mood":"neutral","return_to":"corridor_first","return_label":"Return to the corridor.","on_enter":{"flag":"had_sincere_moment"},"text":["You tell them something true.","Not a confession, exactly. Something smaller. A fact about yourself that has nothing to do with the cover story — something from before the collar, or from the crossing, or just from the particular quality of being in this room with someone who is carrying something heavy.","They listen.","Afterward you both sit with what you said. It was a small thing. But a small true thing is heavier than a large false one.","The cover feels slightly less complete than it did. This is not a problem. This is, perhaps, the point."],"choices":[{"text":"Return to the corridor.","next":"corridor_first","style":"return","set_flag":"cover_integrity_reduced"}]},"merky_confrontation":{"location":"Crew Corridor — Aft Section","mood":"tense","text":["Merky Crabbit is in the corridor. They have been waiting.","'Chaplain.' The word has a different weight than usual.","They set a piece of paper on the shelf between you. A copy of your personnel file. The background you claimed does not match.","'I am not a suspicious person by nature,' Merky says. 'But I have been first mate on this vessel for nine years. And what you told me does not hold together the way things hold together when they are true.'","They wait. The ship moves.","This is a choice about what you are."],"choices":[{"text":"Hold the cover. 'There may be a discrepancy in the file.'","next":"merky_confrontation_hold"},{"text":"[Withholding] Say nothing. Let the silence be the answer.","next":"merky_confrontation_withhold","requires_charism":"withholding","effect":{"composure":1}},{"text":"Drop the cover. Tell them something true.","next":"merky_confrontation_truth","effect":{"communion":1},"set_flag":"cover_integrity_reduced"}]},"merky_confrontation_hold":{"location":"Crew Corridor — Aft Section","mood":"tense","text":["You say it plainly. There may be a discrepancy in the file. Files have discrepancies. You stand in the fact of yourself."],"choices":[{"text":"Continue.","next":"corridor_first","roll":{"stat":"composure","difficulty":9,"successNext":"merky_confrontation_held","partialNext":"merky_confrontation_partial","failNext":"merky_confrontation_fail"}}]},"merky_confrontation_held":{"location":"Crew Corridor — Aft Section","mood":"neutral","text":["Merky looks at you for a long moment. Then they pick up the paper.","'All right,' they say. 'A discrepancy in the file.' They do not say they believe you. They fold the paper and walk away.","Your cover holds. For now."],"choices":[{"text":"Go to the corridor.","next":"corridor_first","set_flag":"merky_cover_held"}]},"merky_confrontation_partial":{"location":"Crew Corridor — Aft Section","mood":"tense","text":["Merky watches the answer arrive. The answer has the shape of a true thing but not the weight.","'Right,' they say. 'A discrepancy.' They leave. They will watch more carefully."],"choices":[{"text":"Go to the corridor.","next":"corridor_first","set_flag":"merky_watching","effect":{"composure":-1}}]},"merky_confrontation_fail":{"location":"Crew Corridor — Aft Section","mood":"tense","on_enter":{"flag":"cover_compromised"},"text":["The hesitation is too long.","Merky does not press. The hesitation said what they needed to hear.","'I see,' they say, picking up the paper. They walk away without another word.","Your cover has been questioned."],"choices":[{"text":"Go to the corridor.","next":"corridor_first","set_flag":"merky_suspicious","effect":{"composure":-2}}]},"merky_confrontation_withhold":{"location":"Crew Corridor — Aft Section","mood":"neutral","text":["You say nothing. Not nothing hostile. The particular quality of a space emptied of intention.","Merky looks at you for a long time. Professionals respect professionals. The kind of stillness you are maintaining is a skill.","'Right,' they say. 'Personnel files.' They pick up the paper and walk away.","Your cover holds. Merky does not entirely believe it. But they respect the craft."],"choices":[{"text":"Go to the corridor.","next":"corridor_first","set_flag":"merky_respects_you","effect":{"composure":2}}]},"merky_confrontation_truth":{"location":"Crew Corridor — Aft Section","mood":"neutral","text":["You tell them something true. Not everything. Something smaller. Something that costs.","A fact about yourself that is not in the cover story.","Merky listens. They pick up the paper. They fold it.","'All right,' they say. Their voice has changed by some small amount. 'I appreciate that.'","Your cover is thinner. But something else is less thin."],"choices":[{"text":"Go to the corridor.","next":"corridor_first","set_flag":"merky_trusts_partial","effect":{"communion":2}}]},"haircut_mess":{"location":"Crew Mess","mood":"uncanny","return_to":"mess_approach","return_label":"Return to the mess.","text":["Haircut is in the mess. She is sitting on the counter near the coffee pot. This is improbable.","She is long-haired, black the way deep water is black. She is looking at you with her full attention. The quality of recognition in her eyes is older than this crossing.","She has already decided something about you. She decided it on the railing. She is just reminding you now.","She closes her eyes briefly. Opens them. This is, you understand, the cat equivalent of several things at once."],"choices":[{"text":"Acknowledge her.","next":"mess_approach","effect":{"communion":1},"reaction":"She accepts the acknowledgement. She was expecting it."},{"text":"Get coffee. Leave her to it.","next":"mess_approach","reaction":"She watches you get coffee. This is also acceptable."}]},"haircut_chapel":{"location":"The Ship's Chapel","mood":"uncanny","return_to":"chapel_waking","return_label":"Return to the chapel.","text":["Haircut is in the chapel. She is sitting on the table next to the {ICON}. She is looking at the {ICON} with the same focused assessment she applies to everything.","She turns to look at you. She has been here for some time. You do not know how she got in.","Her purr: a low rasp that sounds like it has been through a great deal.","She is not here by accident. Nothing Haircut does is by accident."],"choices":[{"text":"Sit with her a while.","next":"chapel_waking","effect":{"doubt":1},"thought":"via_negativa","reaction":"She purrs. The {ICON} is facing the same direction it was. Or perhaps not."},{"text":"Return to the chapel.","next":"chapel_waking","style":"return"}]},"haircut_observation":{"location":"Main Deck — Port Railing","mood":"uncanny","art":"haircut","return_to":"main_deck","return_label":"Return to the deck.","text":["Haircut is on the railing. She is large, long-haired, black. She does not acknowledge you have arrived.","She is doing something complex with her attention — somewhere between the water and somewhere beyond it.","Her purr is present, low, continuous. It will continue after you leave.","You do not speak. You are simply here, in the radius of a creature entirely occupied with being what she is.","She closes one eye. The other remains open. This is probably not theological. Probably.","After a while something in you has quieted. Not resolved — quieted. The crossing continues past this railing.","She is still on the railing when you leave. You do not look back. You know she is there."],"choices":[]}};
